Jupiter Bot Privacy Policy
Effective: September 17, 2024
Last Updated: November 30, 2024

Jupiter Bot is committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring the responsible use of your personal data. This Privacy Policy explains the types of information we collect, how we use and share it, and how you can control your information. By using Jupiter Bot, you agree to the terms outlined in this policy.

To provide and improve our services, Jupiter Bot may collect the following information:  
Guild IDs  
Role IDs  
User IDs  
Channel IDs  
Embed Data: Custom data you configure for embeds or bot-generated content.  

Server and Channel Information:
Metadata related to server and channel usage for bot functions.  
Any settings or configurations you provide through our bot's features (e.g., antinuke settings, moderation configurations).  

We collect and use your information for the following purposes:
To enable and optimize bot functionality within your Discord server.  
To implement server-specific configurations (e.g., moderation, embed setups).   
To detect, prevent, and respond to malicious activities (e.g., server nuking).  
To enhance our services and identify areas for improvement.  
To notify you about updates, service changes, or relevant issues.  

We value your privacy and ensure your data is handled responsibly:  
We do not sell or trade your personal information to third parties.  
In rare cases, we may share information with trusted partners to support our services (e.g., hosting or analytics providers). These partners are contractually obligated to protect your information.  

Data Retention:
We retain your data only for as long as it is necessary to provide our services.  
You can request the deletion of your stored data at any time through the bot's features or by contacting us directly.  

Jupiter Bot empowers users to manage their data effectively:  
Use bot commands to review or modify stored settings and configurations.  
Users can delete guild-specific or user-specific data (e.g., Guild IDs, User IDs, Role IDs, Channel IDs, and embed data) directly through the bot's features or by contacting support. Once deleted, this data is permanently removed from our systems.  

Your Agreement:
By using Jupiter Bot, you agree to this Privacy Policy. We reserve the right to update this policy to reflect changes in our practices or legal requirements. Changes will be communicated via our bot or support channels.  

If you have any questions, concerns, or requests regarding your data, please contact us:  
Email: naitikkjain@gmail.com 
Support Server: https://discord.gg/jupiter

Jupiter Bot is dedicated to maintaining transparency and trust with our users. Thank you for using our services!  
